org.jvoicexml.xml.ccxml
Class Transition

java.lang.Object
  org.jvoicexml.xml.AbstractXmlNode
      org.jvoicexml.xml.ccxml.Transition
All Implemented Interfaces:
CcxmlNode, XmlNode, XmlWritable, Node
public final class Transition
extends AbstractXmlNode

The content of a <transition> specifies the actions to be taken when it is selected. The <transition> are examined by the EHIA in document order.

Constant Field Values

ATTRIBUTE_COND

public static final String ATTRIBUTE_COND
An ECMAScript expression which can be evaluated to true or false. If this attribute is present, it must evaluate to true for the transition to be selected. Note: You can not access the value of a the variable listed in the name attribute as it will not do the assign until the transition has been selected.

See Also:
Constant Field Values

ATTRIBUTE_EVENT

public static final String ATTRIBUTE_EVENT
This is a pattern that indicates a matching event type. Event types are dot-separated strings of arbitrary length. The character * is a wild-card, and will match zero or more characters of the processed event's type name.

See Also:
Constant Field Values

ATTRIBUTE_NAME

public static final String ATTRIBUTE_NAME
An ECMAScript left hand side expression evaluating to a previously defined variable. The value of the attribute will be set to the received event object. The event object can only be referenced by this name while executing the transition .

See Also:
Constant Field Values

ATTRIBUTE_STATE

public static final String ATTRIBUTE_STATE
This indicates the current possible state(s) of the eventprocessor . More than one state name may be specified, separated by white space.

See Also:
Constant Field Values
